cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper involves computer vision and machine learning techniques, specifically using a convolutional neural network to extract depth information from stereo images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a neural network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and refinement techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves using a neural network to improve stereo matching, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
